performance_query.design_brief:
Primary performance target (single-objective): Improve walkability and movement efficiency through the park.

Targets:
• Create a clear, barrier-free loop path (min 2.5 m) linking entrances, play, seating, waterfront, and service node.
• Reduce pedestrian–cyclist conflicts at the entrance and pinch points; clarify right-of-way and crossings.
• Strengthen wayfinding and legibility (signage, sightlines at bends, consistent path hierarchy).

Constraints / co-benefits (not primary targets):
• Add shade where it supports comfort along main walking routes without creating hidden corners.
• Maintain service/emergency access to the toilet/kiosk zone.
• Preserve mature trees when possible; favor nature-based solutions within budget.
